    • addRow

      public void addRow(int tcId, String... rowData) throws IOException

      rowData - Column values for the new row.

    • addRows

      public void addRows(int tcId, List<List<String>> rowsData) throws IOException
      Adds multiple rows to ParameterSet using a list of lists of column values. Each inner list represents a row with column values matching the order of column names in ParameterSet.
      Parameters:
      tcId - The Api from where it should retrieve the data.
      rowsData - A list where each element is a list of column values for a new row.
      Throws:
      IOException

    • deleteMultipleRows

      public void deleteMultipleRows(int tcId, int start, int end) throws IOException
      Deletes multiple rows from ParameterSet based on start and end indices (inclusive). Rearranges row IDs after deletion and updates lastId.
      Parameters:
      tcId - The Api from where it should retrieve the data.
      start - The starting index of rows to delete.
      end - The ending index of rows to delete.
      Throws:

    • deleteRow

      public void deleteRow(int tcId, String columnName, String value) throws IOException
      Deletes the first row in the ParameterSet that contains the specified value in the specified column.
      Parameters:
      tcId - The Api from where it should retrieve the data.
      columnName - The name of the column to search for the value.
